body:
**Description**
<!-- a general description goes here -->
The color of a created SKBitmap is wrong as the red and blue channels are messed up. It has this issue on MacOS, iOS and Android. It is correct on Windows and Linux. 



**Code**

        // It's all you need to recreate this issue. 

        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            int pixelWidth = 800;
            int pixelHeight = 800;

            int bytesPerPixel = 4;
            // the image buffer for the final image stream.
            byte[] imageBuffer = new byte[pixelWidth * pixelHeight * bytesPerPixel];

            for (int y = 0; y < pixelHeight; y++)
            {
                for (int x = 0; x < pixelWidth; x++)
                {
                    int offset = (y * pixelWidth + x) * bytesPerPixel;
                    imageBuffer[offset] = 0;
                    imageBuffer[offset + 1] = 100;
                    imageBuffer[offset + 2] = 255;
                    imageBuffer[offset + 3] = 255;
                }
            }

            // generate the canvas image and save it.
            var bitmap = new SKBitmap(pixelWidth, pixelHeight);
            bitmap.Erase(SKColors.Transparent);
            var intPtr = bitmap.GetPixels();
            Marshal.Copy(imageBuffer, 0, intPtr, imageBuffer.Length);

            using (FileStream fs = new FileStream(args[0], FileMode.CreateNew, FileAccess.ReadWrite))
            {
                using (SKImage skImage = SKImage.FromBitmap(bitmap))
                {
                    SKData skData = skImage.Encode(SKEncodedImageFormat.Png, 100);
                    skData.SaveTo(fs);
                }
            }
        }

**Expected Behavior**

<!-- a general description of what was the expected behavior or result -->
Generated a 800*800 orange image. 

**Actual Behavior**

<!-- a general description of what really happened -->
It generated a 800*800 blue image on MacOS. It has the same issue on Android and iOS.  It's fine on Windows and Linux. 

**Basic Information**

- Version with issue:  <!-- the version of SkiaSharp that has the issue -->2.80.1
- Last known good version:  <!-- the version of SkiaSharp that still working -->None
- IDE:  <!-- Visual Studio / Visual Studio for Mac / MonoDevelop / Visual Studio Code -->VS 2019
- Platform Target Frameworks: <!-- all that apply, remove the platforms that aren't broken or haven't had any testing -->
  - Android: 
  - iOS:  
  - macOS:  
- Target Devices:   <!-- the devices that you noticed this on, e.g. iPhone X -->
  - iPhone 11
  -  Pixel 3
  - Mac Pro
  
</details>

